WEBVTT

1
00:00:57.700 --> 00:00:59.900
<i>Catch them. </i>

2
00:01:01.500 --> 00:01:03.900
<i>Kill them. </i>

3
00:02:44.700 --> 00:02:46.800
What's wrong. Ronnie?

4
00:02:50.500 --> 00:02:52.700
I love you. Jodie.

5
00:03:09.900 --> 00:03:11.500
<i>Suffolk County police. </i>
<i>May I help you?</i>

6
00:03:11.800 --> 00:03:13.300
<i>Everybody's dead. </i>

7
00:03:13.600 --> 00:03:15.300
<i>What do you mean.</i>
<i>"everybody's dead"?</i>

8
00:03:15.700 --> 00:03:17.600
<i>A guy come running</i>
<i>into the bar and says... </i>

9
00:03:17.800 --> 00:03:20.100
<i>... his mother and father are shot. </i>

10
00:03:20.400 --> 00:03:23.000
I've been to a lot of crime scenes.
never seen one like this.

11
00:03:23.200 --> 00:03:25.600
<i>Six members of the family</i>
<i>were found last night... </i>

12
00:03:26.600 --> 00:03:28.900
...in bed. shot...

13
00:03:29.300 --> 00:03:30.900
...and killed.

14
00:03:32.100 --> 00:03:35.600
<i>Killed were car dealer Ronald Defeo.</i>
<i>his wife and four of their children. </i>

15
00:03:35.900 --> 00:03:37.400
<i>The sole survivor of the family... </i>

16
00:03:37.700 --> 00:03:39.800
<i>... 23-year-old</i>
<i>Ronald "Butch" Defeo Jr... </i>

17
00:03:40.100 --> 00:03:41.900
<i>... is said to have discovered</i>
<i>the bodies. </i>

18
00:03:42.200 --> 00:03:44.100
<i>The police state</i>
<i>that for his own safety... </i>

19
00:03:44.400 --> 00:03:46.500
<i>... they're holding him</i>
<i>in protective custody. </i>

20
00:03:46.700 --> 00:03:49.400
<i>Five of the victims were found</i>
<i>shot facedown on their beds. </i>

21
00:03:50.100 --> 00:03:51.700
The sixth was found in a closet.

22
00:03:53.700 --> 00:03:56.100
No one seemed to stir in their sleep.
It's strange.

23
00:03:56.400 --> 00:04:00.100
<i>Suffolk County police have charged</i>
<i>23-year-old Ronald Defeo Jr. </i>

24
00:04:00.300 --> 00:04:02.300
<i>The accused told police</i>
<i>he heard voices... </i>

25
00:04:02.500 --> 00:04:05.700
<i>... coming from within the house.</i>
<i>telling him to murder his family. </i>

26
00:04:20.600 --> 00:04:22.600
Oh. God!

27
00:04:23.200 --> 00:04:24.600
Damn it.

28
00:04:33.900 --> 00:04:35.800
Hi. Michael.

29
00:04:36.200 --> 00:04:37.800
Oh. hey. baby. You okay?

30
00:04:38.100 --> 00:04:40.000
George. what are you doing
to my mom?

31
00:04:40.900 --> 00:04:42.400
Nothing.

32
00:04:42.700 --> 00:04:44.400
- Yet.
- You perv.

33
00:04:52.400 --> 00:04:54.400
Come on up here. little man.

34
00:04:58.700 --> 00:05:00.500
You can make it.

35
00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:03.200
Oh. you're getting heavy.

36
00:05:08.100 --> 00:05:09.700
Did you meet my dad?

37
00:05:11.000 --> 00:05:12.600
No...

38
00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:14.300
...never had the pleasure. pal.

39
00:05:15.900 --> 00:05:17.500
Do I have to call you "Dad" now?

40
00:05:18.400 --> 00:05:20.000
- Guess what.
- What?

41
00:05:20.400 --> 00:05:23.000
- You can call me whatever you want.
- Anything?

42
00:05:23.300 --> 00:05:25.200
- Yep.
- Cool.

43
00:05:25.500 --> 00:05:27.300
- Anything.
- Cool.

44
00:05:27.500 --> 00:05:29.100
Yeah.

45
00:05:29.800 --> 00:05:31.600
- Stinky.
- Sure.

46
00:05:31.900 --> 00:05:33.300
- Poopy-head.
- Yeah.

47
00:05:33.500 --> 00:05:35.300
Crap-monkey-fart.

48
00:05:35.500 --> 00:05:38.700
Okay. we gotta draw the line
somewhere. pal. that does it.

49
00:05:44.400 --> 00:05:46.200
All right.

50
00:05:53.400 --> 00:05:55.400
- This sucks.
- You're not kidding.

51
00:05:55.700 --> 00:05:57.100
Billy.

52
00:05:57.500 --> 00:06:00.400
Look. maybe we'll grab you
something on the way to school.

53
00:06:00.700 --> 00:06:03.600
- What do you say. huh?
- I'm not hungry. I can walk to school.

54
00:06:03.800 --> 00:06:06.300
No. you can't. and get
your feet off the chair.

55
00:06:07.000 --> 00:06:09.000
I'll drop you a couple blocks away.
Nobody'd see.

56
00:06:09.300 --> 00:06:11.200
- Mom. I'm 12 years old.
- Before you plan...

57
00:06:11.400 --> 00:06:14.100
...your retirement party. we're gonna
drop you off at school.

58
00:06:14.400 --> 00:06:16.300
We got a big day.

59
00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:19.500
Why? Where are you guys going?

60
00:06:21.300 --> 00:06:23.900
- Mom. can you help me?
- Oh. Michael.

61
00:06:28.900 --> 00:06:31.000
Houses here are way out
of our price range. Kath.

62
00:06:31.300 --> 00:06:32.900
Not according to this.

63
00:06:33.100 --> 00:06:36.600
- Well. then it's gotta be true.
- Think positive. babe.

64
00:06:36.900 --> 00:06:40.200
I'm positive that houses here
are out of our price range.

65
00:06:42.700 --> 00:06:44.500
Look. when the business
is going good...

66
00:06:44.700 --> 00:06:45.900
...we're gonna...
- There.

67
00:06:46.100 --> 00:06:47.300
- What?
- That's it.

68
00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:49.200
- Look.
- Honey.

69
00:06:49.300 --> 00:06:51.000
Baby. look. 412 Ocean Avenue.

70
00:06:57.600 --> 00:06:59.400
- It's beautiful.
- What?

71
00:07:15.500 --> 00:07:17.900
Look at how friendly they are here.
honey.

72
00:07:18.200 --> 00:07:20.600
They get like that when they think
they'll make a sale.

73
00:07:20.800 --> 00:07:24.800
Let's just play it cool. Kath.
Kathy. Katherine.

74
00:07:25.700 --> 00:07:27.200
Or not.

75
00:07:34.800 --> 00:07:36.700
- Hi there.
- I'm Katherine Lutz.

76
00:07:37.000 --> 00:07:39.100
Well. just call me Edith.
This is your husband?

77
00:07:39.300 --> 00:07:41.700
- George.
- This is an amazing house.

78
00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:45.800
You are going to love it.
Just follow me in here.

79
00:07:46.900 --> 00:07:49.400
Careful on the steps there.

80
00:08:06.400 --> 00:08:09.400
Holy shit.

81
00:08:10.400 --> 00:08:11.900
Excuse me.

82
00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:14.300
Let me show you
the rest of the house.

83
00:08:15.300 --> 00:08:17.600
This... This is a mistake.

84
00:08:17.900 --> 00:08:19.100
How's that?

85
00:08:19.300 --> 00:08:21.300
No. I mean your ad in the paper.

86
00:08:22.700 --> 00:08:24.200
This is...

87
00:08:24.400 --> 00:08:26.500
It's gotta be a misprint.
I'm a contractor...

88
00:08:26.700 --> 00:08:29.000
...and I know what a place
like this should cost.

89
00:08:29.300 --> 00:08:30.500
And. you know. if this is...

90
00:08:30.800 --> 00:08:34.300
Well. if this is true. then this is a...
The deal of a lifetime.

91
00:08:34.700 --> 00:08:36.800
And what is wrong with that?

92
00:08:37.900 --> 00:08:40.500
- Come on.
- I love it.

93
00:08:43.900 --> 00:08:47.500
- There's a vibrant history here.
- Vibrant history. George.

94
00:08:47.900 --> 00:08:51.500
In fact. the house was built
in 1692. at least the basement.

95
00:08:52.200 --> 00:08:54.500
The rest of the house was added
from that foundation.

96
00:08:54.800 --> 00:08:57.200
It's one of the oldest Dutch Colonials
in Long Island.

97
00:08:57.500 --> 00:08:58.800
Wow. that's impressive.

98
00:08:58.900 --> 00:09:01.900
This room would be perfect
for children. if you have any.

99
00:09:02.300 --> 00:09:06.200
And the view's...
Well. have a look for yourselves.

100
00:09:09.000 --> 00:09:10.600
There's a boathouse.

101
00:09:10.800 --> 00:09:12.800
Oh. all you need now
is a boat. right?

102
00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:15.900
Actually. George has a speedboat.

103
00:09:16.700 --> 00:09:19.900
This place sounds
like it's made for you.

104
00:09:30.400 --> 00:09:33.300
And this is your basement.

105
00:09:33.500 --> 00:09:36.600
As you can see.
it's very spacious.

106
00:09:36.900 --> 00:09:39.500
It can be a game room.
a playroom.

107
00:09:39.800 --> 00:09:41.500
Well. let's... Let's have a look.

108
00:09:47.400 --> 00:09:50.300
I'll just wait up here.

109
00:09:56.100 --> 00:09:58.200
Yep. looks like a basement.

110
00:09:58.500 --> 00:10:00.400
So. what do you guys think?

111
00:10:00.700 --> 00:10:04.800
- I think you look foxy in that skirt.
- Will you stop it? Come on.

112
00:10:16.600 --> 00:10:18.600
Yes. yes. okay?

113
00:10:19.100 --> 00:10:21.900
It's a value. It's a value
for people with money.

114
00:10:22.200 --> 00:10:25.200
Okay. look. if we do this. we're
gonna be eating dry wall for a year.

115
00:10:25.500 --> 00:10:27.100
We deserve this. George.

116
00:10:27.300 --> 00:10:29.300
You deserve this.

117
00:10:29.600 --> 00:10:32.200
How many times you tell me
how hard you work for so little.

118
00:10:32.500 --> 00:10:35.100
- Kathy...
- Maybe today is the day it all pays off.

119
00:10:35.900 --> 00:10:38.000
- We'll make sacrifices.
- Huge sacrifices.

120
00:10:38.200 --> 00:10:41.100
Yeah. I understand that.
Listen. honey...

121
00:10:41.400 --> 00:10:43.500
...this is the life we want.

122
00:10:59.200 --> 00:11:01.300
- We're happy?
- Yes. we're happy.

123
00:11:01.500 --> 00:11:03.900
She's happy. I'm broke.

124
00:11:06.100 --> 00:11:07.500
Hold on. hold on. hold on.

125
00:11:07.800 --> 00:11:11.800
So look. I gotta ask.
what's the catch?

126
00:11:13.100 --> 00:11:15.400
There's always a catch.

127
00:11:16.900 --> 00:11:21.200
There was a tragedy. a crime...

128
00:11:21.600 --> 00:11:24.200
...a murder.
- I'm sorry. what?

129
00:11:24.500 --> 00:11:26.300
In the house?

130
00:11:27.200 --> 00:11:28.600
Several people. a family.

131
00:11:30.900 --> 00:11:33.200
But. you know. we've moved on.
the whole town.

132
00:11:33.500 --> 00:11:36.000
It is a distant memory now.

133
00:11:37.000 --> 00:11:39.100
And the house is fine.

134
00:11:39.400 --> 00:11:40.900
Really.

135
00:11:41.200 --> 00:11:43.700
Doesn't it seem kind of strange
to buy this house. honey?

136
00:11:43.900 --> 00:11:46.100
Well. houses don't kill people.

137
00:11:46.400 --> 00:11:48.600
People kill people.

138
00:11:49.900 --> 00:11:52.800
Just... Excuse us.

139
00:11:54.500 --> 00:11:56.700
Do you think we can make it work?

140
00:12:02.200 --> 00:12:04.000
You know what?

141
00:12:04.500 --> 00:12:07.500
You want it.
then we're gonna make it work.

142
00:12:07.900 --> 00:12:09.900
- Really?
- I'll work out of the basement...

143
00:12:10.100 --> 00:12:11.900
...and you can. well...

144
00:12:13.000 --> 00:12:14.800
...sell one of the kids.
- Hey.

145
00:12:15.600 --> 00:12:17.000
A little one.

146
00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:33.700
We're rich! We're rich!

147
00:12:34.300 --> 00:12:36.900
We're rich in something.
but it ain't money.

148
00:12:39.600 --> 00:12:41.000
Wait.

149
00:13:22.000 --> 00:13:24.600
- You say your prayers?
- Yep. said them twice.

150
00:13:24.900 --> 00:13:28.500
- What did you pray for?
- Lf I tell you. it won't come true.

151
00:13:29.800 --> 00:13:31.400
Why don't you tell him the truth.

152
00:13:31.700 --> 00:13:34.100
- What?
- Praying doesn't do any good.

153
00:13:34.600 --> 00:13:36.000
William.

154
00:13:36.300 --> 00:13:39.700
Nobody answered me when
I asked for Dad to be kept alive.

155
00:13:41.900 --> 00:13:43.800
Don't say that.

156
00:13:48.400 --> 00:13:51.300
Sometimes things happen in life
that can't be explained. Billy.

157
00:13:57.400 --> 00:13:59.000
Billy. look at me.

158
00:14:00.600 --> 00:14:03.300
I need you to give George
a chance. okay?

159
00:14:04.500 --> 00:14:07.600
You're not being disloyal
to Dad by liking George.

160
00:14:09.100 --> 00:14:11.600
He doesn't want to be anything
but your friend...

161
00:14:12.300 --> 00:14:14.000
...and maybe one day
something more.

162
00:14:14.700 --> 00:14:17.600
Nobody will ever
replace your dad. honey.

163
00:14:20.300 --> 00:14:21.900
For you too?

164
00:14:22.700 --> 00:14:24.300
For me too.

165
00:14:39.800 --> 00:14:41.500
How's Billy?

166
00:14:41.900 --> 00:14:43.500
He'll be fine.

167
00:14:45.100 --> 00:14:47.200
- First call.
- First call.

168
00:14:50.000 --> 00:14:53.300
- Lutz residence. how may I help you?
<i>- Can I talk to my daughter. please?</i>

169
00:14:53.700 --> 00:14:57.800
Yeah. sure. she's...
She's right here. Okay.

170
00:14:58.300 --> 00:15:00.800
Your mother's gotta stop
gushing over me. seriously.

171
00:15:01.100 --> 00:15:02.900
It's embarrassing now.

172
00:15:03.500 --> 00:15:05.200
<i>Hello?</i>

173
00:15:06.100 --> 00:15:09.100
- Hey. Ma.
<i>- Hi. </i>

174
00:15:09.500 --> 00:15:11.700
No. we're all moved in.

175
00:15:13.800 --> 00:15:15.800
- Yeah. Ma.
- Are you cold?

176
00:15:18.200 --> 00:15:20.000
No. Ma.

177
00:15:20.900 --> 00:15:21.700
Yeah.

178
00:17:27.000 --> 00:17:30.000
- What is it. baby?
- Nothing.

179
00:17:31.800 --> 00:17:34.700
- Are you okay. baby?
- No.

180
00:17:35.400 --> 00:17:37.200
I don't feel well.

181
00:17:52.800 --> 00:17:54.700
- Give me a kiss.
- I can do it. I can do it.

182
00:17:55.000 --> 00:17:56.400
No. you can't.

183
00:17:57.100 --> 00:17:59.700
Come here. come here.

184
00:18:01.700 --> 00:18:04.400
Honey. I'm gonna
make you some tea.

185
00:18:12.100 --> 00:18:15.100
How many brothers and sisters
do you have?

186
00:18:18.100 --> 00:18:20.800
- Chelsea?
- Hey. Mommy.

187
00:18:21.100 --> 00:18:23.300
Hi. hon. Who are you talking to?

188
00:18:23.500 --> 00:18:27.000
- The girl who lives in my closet.
- Oh. yeah?

189
00:18:27.200 --> 00:18:29.400
- And what's her name?
- Jodie.

190
00:18:30.600 --> 00:18:34.000
You know there are plenty of other
little girls to play with in town too?

191
00:18:34.200 --> 00:18:36.400
I know. but Jodie says
they're all mean.

192
00:18:38.600 --> 00:18:39.800
Is that Jodie?

193
00:18:45.600 --> 00:18:48.000
No. that's someone else.

194
00:18:48.200 --> 00:18:49.700
Who?

195
00:18:49.900 --> 00:18:52.600
I'm not supposed to say who.

196
00:18:54.500 --> 00:18:56.900
She says it's an A-hole.

197
00:18:57.200 --> 00:18:59.600
You are not allowed
to say that word.

198
00:19:19.900 --> 00:19:22.000
George. George.

199
00:19:22.500 --> 00:19:25.200
- Look what I found.
- What is that? Where'd you find that?

200
00:19:25.400 --> 00:19:26.600
Harry and I found it.

201
00:19:27.600 --> 00:19:29.800
- Where?
- In the basement.

202
00:19:30.500 --> 00:19:32.000
Not the basement.

203
00:19:32.200 --> 00:19:34.200
My office.

204
00:19:36.100 --> 00:19:38.500
You listen to me.
You don't go down there.

205
00:19:39.300 --> 00:19:40.800
Understand?

206
00:19:48.600 --> 00:19:51.200
Guys. would you help me
with the groceries?

207
00:19:53.200 --> 00:19:55.500
Go on. go help your mom.

208
00:20:00.600 --> 00:20:02.400
I'm sorry.

209
00:20:04.100 --> 00:20:05.500
Go on.

210
00:20:20.100 --> 00:20:23.000
- How are you feeling?
- Good. good.

211
00:20:24.100 --> 00:20:26.700
I found a babysitter off a board
at the grocery store.

212
00:20:27.000 --> 00:20:28.200
Billy will love that.

213
00:20:28.400 --> 00:20:30.300
How about we call her
the young-adult-sitter?

214
00:20:33.100 --> 00:20:34.300
Where's Chelsea?

215
00:20:36.400 --> 00:20:37.900
Where's Chelsea?

216
00:20:47.700 --> 00:20:49.400
Chelsea?

217
00:20:57.100 --> 00:20:58.300
Chelsea?

218
00:20:58.600 --> 00:21:00.400
Chelsea!

219
00:21:06.900 --> 00:21:08.300
Chelsea.

220
00:21:08.400 --> 00:21:09.800
Hey. give me your hand.

221
00:21:10.200 --> 00:21:11.400
Give me your hand. sweetie.

222
00:21:11.700 --> 00:21:14.900
- Chelsea. go to George.
- Come on. Hey. give me your hand.

223
00:21:20.800 --> 00:21:23.400
What were you thinking?
You could have fallen in the water.

224
00:21:23.600 --> 00:21:25.500
Jodie wanted to see the boat.

225
00:21:28.800 --> 00:21:30.800
Somebody should have been
watching you.

226
00:22:31.000 --> 00:22:33.700
Billy. get up.

227
00:22:34.400 --> 00:22:36.800
Billy. I gotta go pee.

228
00:24:55.600 --> 00:24:57.000
Chelsea.

229
00:25:41.700 --> 00:25:43.300
Goddamn it. Harry.

230
00:25:46.500 --> 00:25:49.200
Seriously. You trying to kill me?

231
00:26:56.800 --> 00:26:58.200
Come on. get away from there.

232
00:26:58.400 --> 00:27:00.100
Hey. that's enough.

233
00:27:00.700 --> 00:27:02.300
Hey!

234
00:27:11.000 --> 00:27:13.300
George? Hon. what are you
doing down here?

235
00:27:14.400 --> 00:27:17.500
It's the only place
that's warm in this damn house.

236
00:27:18.800 --> 00:27:20.900
Somebody keeps opening
the windows.

237
00:27:25.500 --> 00:27:27.100
What is that?

238
00:27:29.200 --> 00:27:31.000
You tell me.

239
00:27:32.600 --> 00:27:35.400
- Why don't you come back to bed.
- No. I can't sleep.

240
00:27:35.600 --> 00:27:37.200
I'm sorry. baby.

241
00:27:37.500 --> 00:27:39.200
Don't...

242
00:27:39.500 --> 00:27:42.100
Don't talk to me like
I'm one of your kids. okay?

243
00:27:42.400 --> 00:27:44.800
- What?
- That goddamn dog woke me up.

244
00:27:46.600 --> 00:27:48.200
Billy's dog.

245
00:27:50.300 --> 00:27:51.600
Found him in the boathouse.

246
00:27:53.100 --> 00:27:55.500
- But you locked it.
- Yeah.

247
00:27:55.700 --> 00:27:58.200
Hey. and guess
what I found in Billy's room.

248
00:28:06.600 --> 00:28:08.600
You ready to talk
about those keys?

249
00:28:08.900 --> 00:28:11.900
There's not a lot in this world can't
be solved with an apology. Billy.

250
00:28:12.200 --> 00:28:14.500
I'm not apologizing
